<a href="#0" id="0">In this paper, we develop a system for the task of predicting the grammaticality of sentences, and present a dataset of learner sentences rated for grammaticality.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">We create a dataset of grammatical and ungrammatical sentences written by English language learners, labeled on an ordinal scale for grammaticality.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">Each sentence was annotated on a scale from 1 to 4 as described below, with 4 being the most grammatical.</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">We report performance in terms of Pearson ’ s r between the averaged 1 – 4 human labels and unrounded system predictions.</a>
